node.text:
You can actually watch my office morph over the course of this video... thus rad as hell and completely accidental. 

Dang, I don’t remember Suorin stuff being this solid.  Suorin has come a long way since I last tried their products.  This Suorin Air Pro is worlds better than I remember Suorin being.  Full rich flavorful coil heads, Smooth ( but more loose ) draw,  nice sized battery and pod. 

It's kinda hard to not dig the Suorin Air Pro. Even with the slightly bigger size, I really like having that bigger battery. The pods / coil heads seem to have a very very average life.  The Suorin Air Pro pods start off REALLY strong and crispy and flavorful.  After 3-4 pods the flavor dips a little and the crispy drops a little.  It settles into a highly decent vape for the rest of its life. 

#vaping #vapers #grimmgreen #grimmarmy #vapecommunity #vapefam #vapelife #vapeworld #vapeworldwide

A little bit in love with @boxermod Classic. As I said in the video, If you haven't held or tried a 3D Printed mod recently, give it another shot.  Maybe i'm late to the party here, but 3D printing really has come a long way.  This feels like a finished consumer products and much more durable than "home 3D Printed" devices in the past. 

DNA150C is pretty snappy and nice, it can do a lot that I don't care about, but I know lots of people will.  I wish it had a solid bypass mode and I wish the UI wasn't so awful. 

#vaping #vapers #grimmgreen #grimmarmy #vapecommunity #vapefam #vapelife #vapeworld #vapeworldwide

It's the April 2021 Office Refresh, now with more hot Philips hue action.  Just wanted to share this mostly frustrating adventure I had in my office. I had a vision and my rad-as-hell wife helped me achieve that vision.. mostly.  I'm sure there were 100 better ways to do what I did, but my way worked great.  The "brackets" we used for the outdoor strip above my desk were the included brackets that came with the Philips Huge srtip.  I should have specified that in the video. 

Despite using all sorts of double sided tape and foam, I still have the occasional acoustic tile just fall to the ground.  Even the 30lb permanent-bonding tape can't hold onto the foam.  This must be magic effing acoustic foam.  Overall, really very happy with my April 2021 Office Refresh. For anyone curious, I was watching an MXPX livestream on my computer. 

.
#vaping #vapers #grimmgreen #grimmarmy #vapecommunity #vapefam #vapelife #vapeworld #vapeworldwide

Have you tried the abyss? It’s slowly sneaking it’s way into my “daily carry” category.  Still flawed IMO, but I can’t not enjoy the form factor. 

Side note: I’m really proud of this video. I had a lot of fun shooting it and editing it.  Been trying to have a better attitude lately and I hope that shows in this vid. ☄️🐉

Pleasantly surprised by this little single coil flavor banger RDA.  Before people go bananas, I know I didn't mention everyones favorite The WASP Nano.  Totally another less-expensive option and a solid single coil RDA.  I happen to like the Claymore RDA much more than the Wasp Nano. 

Build deck is on point, flavor is on point, fit and finish are quite solid ( except for the colored plastic parts ) Nothing crazy new, not re-inventing the wheel.  Just a solid little single coil flavor banger.  Really enjoy the Claymore RDA.

Here we go with the Nautilus Prime.  Honestly... it holds up pretty well.  The restricted lung is real nice, the MTL quality holds up, but i've been having some short life spans of these MTL coil heads.  They have been a little bit hit and miss. 

As for the device itself? pretty cool.  Feels a little "cheap" sometimes and like I said, the colors leave a lot to be desired.  With so many MTL / Restricted lung AIO's out on the market right now.  I think Aspire is going to have to step up their game a little bit in order to stand out.

Don't think I can add anything else to the gushing over the Caliburn G.  As of right now, it's really the only pod I care to use.  Superb and flavorful MTL. Just a big fan of the Caliburn G.  Would recommend again and again 

@myuwell

So the IVO RTA is a pretty cheaply priced and cheaply made MTL RTA.  it will give you a nice tight MTL vape with some good flavor. But that's kinda it.  I don't super enjoy this tank, I don't like the airflow and the overall construction of the IVO RTA. 

As I said in the video, the IVO RTA a very "meh" MTL RTA.  I would put it in the "it's fine" category. Not super enjoyable, not really innovative or new in any way.  This is going to be a pass from me. 

.
.
